## Assign payment method

> Sample Request

```json
{
  "apiKey": "<%= config.auth %>",
  "paymentMethodId": "566595c8ce88ccec69328566",
  "billId": "579b695decea110719b1874d"
}
```

> 200 Response

```json
{
  "success": true
}
```

> 400 Response

```json
{
  "message": "No payment method found by that ID."
}
```

Assign a linked payment method to pay a specific bill. This is required when a company's `requiredPayment` is defined as `card` or `bank`.

### HTTP Request

`POST <%= config.host %>/payment/assign`

### Post Parameters

Param | Description
----- | -----------
`paymentMethodId` | Payment method ID.
`billId` | Bill ID to assign.

### Returns

Returns a `200` status code if the payment method was successfully assigned. Returns an error otherwise.